#: of numpy.random.RandomState.uniform:65
msgid "The probability density function of the uniform distribution is"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/random/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.random.RandomState.uniform:67
msgid ""
"p(x) = \\frac{1}{b - a}\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/random/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.random.RandomState.uniform:69
msgid "anywhere within the interval ``[a, b)``, and zero elsewhere."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/random/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.random.RandomState.uniform:71
msgid ""
"When ``high`` == ``low``, values of ``low`` will be returned. If ``high`` < "
"``low``, the results are officially undefined and may eventually raise an "
"error, i.e. do not rely on this function to behave when passed arguments "
"satisfying that inequality condition. The ``high`` limit may be included in "
"the returned array of floats due to floating-point rounding in the equation "
"``low + (high-low) * random_sample()``. For example:"
msgstr ""

